[00:23.27] Solemn faced
[00:25.05] The village settles down
[00:28.69] Undetected by the stars
[00:34.23] And the hangman plays the mandolin before he goes to sleep
[00:43.27] And the last thing on his mind
[00:49.36] Is the wild eyed boy imprisoned
[00:52.65] 'Neath the covered wooden shaft
[00:59.33] Folds the rope into its bag
[01:05.95] Blows his pipe of smoulders
[01:08.84] Blankets smoke into the room
[01:14.60] And the day will end for some
[01:21.86] As the night begins for one
[01:35.36] 
[01:31.87] Staring through the message in his eyes
[01:37.11] Lies a solitary son
[01:42.98] From the mountain called Freecloud
[01:46.25] Where the eagle dare not fly
[01:52.11] And the patience in his sigh
[01:58.23] Gives no indication
[02:01.31] For the townsmen to decide
